# Access and security guardrails

Default access class is A0/A1: no external access, local files, mocks, or sandbox only.

## Access policy

- A0 no external access: allowed.
- A1 local files/mock: allowed.
- A2 read-only sandbox: requires review.
- A3 write non-production: forbidden without ADR and approval.
- A4 production: forbidden in the initial phase.

## Security and compliance

- Never commit secrets, real tokens, private keys, passwords, or personal credentials.
- Do not use real personal data in prompts, tests, fixtures, or examples without documented privacy review.
- Use least privilege and dedicated test identities when access is approved.
- Document purpose, owner, data class, logging, rollback/revocation, and tests before A2+ access.
- Map critical changes to GDPR, DORA, NIS2, EU AI Act, IVASS, or other applicable controls when relevant.
